Tylopus sigma
- 
Golovatch 1983
: 182 (M); 1984: 69 (M, D); 
Golovatch and Enghoff 1993
: 90 (M, D); 
Enghoff et al. 2004
: 40 (R); 
Likhitrakarn et al. 2010
: 26 (R, D).

Length 18-19 mm (♂), width of midbody pro- and metazonae 1.0-1.1 and 1.5-1.7 mm (♂), respectively (versus length 25 mm and width of midbody metazonae 1.6 mm, as given in the original description (
Attems 1953
)). Lectotype 18 mm long, 1.0 and 1.5 mm wide on midbody pro- and metazonae, respectively. Coloration of alcohol material after long preservation rather uniformly brown (Fig. 12
A-G
) (versus blackish brown with edges of paraterga and legs yellowish brown, as given in the description (
Attems 1953
)).
